included.description:
As an extension of the White House Foster Care & Technology Hackathon, the objective of this Data Challenge is to recruit and retain foster families in New York City.  The intention of this interdisciplinary & experiential open-ended event is to utilize scientific data, design and digital solutions in useful and positive ways.

Although the data challenge is complete, our work is far from finished. Authorea is working with the City of New York's Administration for Children's Services to evaluate the feasibility of implementation of the proposed solutions. Authorea, together with the some of New York's finest change agents, is committed to using scientific data, design and digital solutions in useful and positive ways to help the city's most vulnerable kids.

included.description:
Arbnyc.com is an online social community for young Arab-American professionals. Our team interviews users to test solutions that serve new and incoming students from the Arab world inside the heart of the city. 

The platform provides a safe-thinking-space for artists, writers, thinkers, and creatives who recently moved to New York City, or want to connect with new folks to share similar backgrounds and stories. 

The blog includes write-ups and reviews for youth-based programs, university conferences for an audience with interests in The Middle East and North Africa (MENA) region coupled with the experiences of being in New York City. 

This project started as a Thesis deliverable for my Masterâs in Anthropology from the Graduate Center, City University of New York, NYC.
